
[1]capsule

   CAPSULE, n.

   1. The seed vessel of a plant; a dry membranaceous hollow pericarp,
   opening differently in different plants. It is composed of valves or
   outer covering, partitions, the columella or central pillar, and cells.

   2. A small saucer, made of clay for roasting samples or ores, or for
   melting them.
